# ── DeskCloud — NATIVE integration (not widgets). Each Desk is env-gated: it
# activates ONLY when its VITE_*DESK_URL is set. Leave all unset (default) to
# keep the app on its own first-party features, completely unaffected. Optional
# VITE_*DESK_PK defaults to "pk_demo" when unset. The example values below are
# the LIVE DeskCloud endpoints — production sets these; nothing is hardcoded in
# source. Data is fetched via the published @heejun/deskcloud SDK (browser pk_
# clients) and rendered with the app's OWN components + design tokens.
#
# SECURITY: only publishable (pk_) keys belong here / in the client bundle.
# NEVER put a secret sk_ key in any VITE_* var — those reach the browser.

# SurveyDesk — in-app product feedback. When set, the native DeskCloud panel
# (bottom-left launcher → drawer) shows a "Feedback" tab that loads the active
# survey and submits responses. Distinct from the first-party /support inquiry
# board (which posts to the desk-platform public inquiry API — see below).
# VITE_SURVEYDESK_URL="https://surveydesk-api.vercel.app"
# VITE_SURVEYDESK_PK="pk_demo"

# desk-platform — public inquiry board backend for the first-party /support
# route (POST/GET /api/v1/apps/PromptMarket/inquiries). No key needed; the API
# is public + CORS-open and LIVE at the default base, so this is unset in prod.
# Override only for local desk-platform dev (default api port 6090).
# VITE_DESK_PLATFORM_URL="https://desk-platform.vercel.app"

# ChangelogDesk — in-app "What's new". When set, a native navbar button (with an
# unread badge) opens a dropdown of published changelog entries.
# VITE_CHANGELOGDESK_URL="https://changelogdesk-api.vercel.app"
# VITE_CHANGELOGDESK_PK="pk_demo"

# NotifyDesk — notification bell. When set, the navbar bell renders the LIVE
# NotifyDesk inbox (signed-in users) natively in place of the app's first-party
# static bell; unset falls back to the first-party bell. No separate floating bell.
# VITE_NOTIFYDESK_URL="https://notifydesk-api.vercel.app"
# VITE_NOTIFYDESK_PK="pk_demo"

# SearchDesk — secondary global search palette. Bound to mod+/ (Ctrl/Cmd + /) so
# it never collides with the app's own catalog-aware ⌘K command palette (a core
# feature, always primary). Rendered natively as a sibling of the ⌘K palette.
# VITE_SEARCHDESK_URL="https://searchdesk-api.vercel.app"
# VITE_SEARCHDESK_PK="pk_demo"

# ReviewDesk — ratings & testimonials wall. When set, the native DeskCloud panel
# shows a "Reviews" tab (rating aggregate + approved/featured reviews).
# VITE_REVIEWDESK_URL="https://reviewdesk-api.vercel.app"
# VITE_REVIEWDESK_PK="pk_demo"

# ModerationDesk — report content. When set, the native DeskCloud panel shows a
# "Report" tab that submits abuse reports. Does not replace first-party admin
# moderation tooling.
# VITE_MODERATIONDESK_URL="https://16.176.210.195.nip.io/moderation"
# VITE_MODERATIONDESK_PK="pk_demo"

# ── Available DeskCloud modules intentionally NOT wired here ──────────────────
# CommunityDesk — the app ships a first-party /community route (a CORE feature),
# so it is never replaced by a Desk feed.
# VITE_COMMUNITYDESK_URL="https://communitydesk-api.vercel.app"
# VITE_COMMUNITYDESK_PK="pk_demo"
# MediaDesk — no matching first-party feature to fold in (documented for future use).
# VITE_MEDIADESK_URL="https://16.176.210.195.nip.io/media"
# VITE_MEDIADESK_PK="pk_demo"
# RealtimeDesk = presence/live, ChatDesk = DM/chat. The app's core messaging
# (/messages) is first-party; these are documented for future use.
# VITE_REALTIMEDESK_URL="https://16.176.210.195.nip.io/realtime"
# VITE_REALTIMEDESK_PK="pk_demo"
# VITE_CHATDESK_URL="https://16.176.210.195.nip.io/chat"
# VITE_CHATDESK_PK="pk_demo"
